Top: in this experiment you will complete a memory test for the images and colored frames that were presented yesterday.
Middle_Top: the memory test will include previously seen AND new images.

Top: images will be presented on the screen one at a time.
Middle_Top: six blocks of images will be presented.

Top: some of the images will portray scenes with emotional content.
Middle_Top: if you become uncomfortable please remember that you can leave the experiment at any point without penalty.

Top: you will first report whether you remember previously seeing each image, and your confidence in your response.
Top_Bottom: when responding refer to the scale below:
Middle_Bottom: use your keyboard to submit your response.

Top: if you DO NOT remember seeing the image previously, use your left hand to respond using either the 'A', 'S', or 'D' keys.
if you DO remember seeing the image previously, use your right hand to respond using either the 'J', 'K', or 'L' keys.

Top_Bottom: keep both hands on the keyboard once you begin the memory test.
Middle_Bottom: we are interested in your first reaction, so respond at your own pace but please report your initial "gut reaction".

TBMT_int: please use the full range of the scale.

Top: example of what you will see when reporting your memory for the image:
Middle_Bottom: If you very confidently remembered this image you would press 'L'.
Bottom_Top: If you very confidently did not remember, you would press 'A'.

Top: for remembered images, your memory and associated confidence will also be tested for the frame color which surrounded the image.
Top_Bottom: when responding refer to the scale below:
Middle_Bottom: use your keyboard to submit your response.

Top: if the color of the frame around the image differs from what you remember, use your left hand to respond using either the 'A', 'S', or 'D' keys.
if the color of the frame around the image matches what you remember, use your right hand to respond using either the 'J', 'K', or 'L' keys.
example of what you will see when reporting your memory for the frame color:
Middle_Bottom: If you very confidently remembered a yellow frame around the image you would press 'L'.
Bottom_Top: If you very confidently remembered another color around the frame, you would press 'A'.

Middle_Top: this is the end of the instructions
